[KAIDOU]
That score isn't that bad!

242
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:26,333
[SAIKI] Don't try to comfort me.
I don't need it.

243
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:29,125
The big thing we learned today
is that this trick pencil

244
00:09:29,208 --> 00:09:30,833
my dad once had
really does work.

245
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:33,291
Wait, your dad left behind
that lucky pencil for you?

246
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:34,500
Yep.

247
00:09:34,583 --> 00:09:36,166
[KAIDOU]
How'd you score that high

248
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:38,125
just by rolling a pencil?
Are you psychic?

249
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:39,333
[NENDOU]
Probably!

250
00:09:39,416 --> 00:09:41,791
I don't see
your name on this.

251
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:43,500
It's there...

252
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:45,833
right near the bottom.

253
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:49,333
[man singing in Japanese]

254
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:54,500
♪

255
00:09:57,041 --> 00:10:01,375
[MAN] So down the drain.
My life is over. What a pain.

256
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:03,458
[SAIKI] The second I take off
the telepathy blocking ring,

257
00:10:03,541 --> 00:10:04,958
I hear this stuff.

258
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:07,583
Peoples' thoughts
are always so exhausting.

259
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:09,375
This guy's got it
pretty bad.

260
00:10:09,458 --> 00:10:12,333
Wait-- I could swear
I've heard that voice before.

261
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:14,125
[MAN]
Floating in the water.

262
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:15,458
[sobbing]
[SAIKI] Nope.

263
00:10:15,541 --> 00:10:17,458
False alarm,
and I'm going home now.

264
00:10:17,541 --> 00:10:19,458
--Master?
--[SAIKI] Wrong guy.

265
00:10:19,541 --> 00:10:22,041
Oh, Master, I've never needed
your help and wisdom

266
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:23,500
more than I do
right now!

267
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:24,750
[SAIKI]
I said "wrong guy"!

268
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:26,125
Master! I beg of you!

269
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,833
Join my magic act
as my new assistant!

270
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,666
[MAN]
Ladies and gentlemen,

271
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:33,583
our next performer's been on
<i>Miraculous Magic Show</i> --

272
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:37,750
The illusionist you've all been
waiting for: Uryoku Chouno!

273
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:40,625
--Tres bien!
--[audience cheering]

274
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:42,125
[MAN]
What a response!

275
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:44,250
[SAIKI]
How's he more popular than ever?

276
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:46,500
His act seems just as terrible
as I remember!

277
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:49,750
Of course, the real question is
how did I get talked into this?

278
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,541
[CHOUNO]
I have a show booked tonight,

279
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,833
but my assistant, Michael,
got in an accident.

280
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:55,625
[SAIKI]
What? Did he die?

281
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:58,083
[CHOUNO]
Fortunately, he didn't die.

282
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:00,458
But he did say he
couldn't do tonight's show.

283
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:03,708
I asked anyone I could think of
to be my substitute assistant,

284
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:06,000
but they all said no.
When I needed them most,

285
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:07,833
my friends vanished
into thin air.

286
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:09,666
It feels like
a really bad illusion.

287
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:11,250
[SAIKI]
That's sad. I guess.

288
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,250
[CHOUNO] I got so desperate,
I even asked my mom.

289
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,916
It wound up looking
really terrible.

290
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,625
[SAIKI]
Don't say that about your mom.

291
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:18,666
Please, master,
can you just help me out

292
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,125
with tonight's show?
I'm busy.

293
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:22,500
[CHOUNO] This is the biggest
show of my life!

294
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:25,083
Please! My love,
my darling wife who left me

295
00:11:25,166 --> 00:11:27,916
is coming to see it!
This is my last best chance...

296
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,708
to win back her love...

297
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:33,708
[sobs]
You're not listening?

298
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,041
[CHOUNO]
Because you're annoying.

299
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,625
What kind of master
are you?

300
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,041
[SAIKI]
When you referred to her

301
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,875
as your "darling wife,"
I cringed.

302
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:42,083
[CHOUNO]
How could you ignore the needy!

303
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:44,250
This is the classic
body-cutting trick.

304
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,000
I put all my savings
into this box.

305
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:48,000
A new one would cost
1.2 million yen,

306
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,916
so I bought
this used one for 1.18.

307
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,541
[SAIKI] You should've
bought it new.

308
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:53,583
But it came with
no instructions!

309
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:55,333
Michael and I tried
doing the trick

310
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:57,833
dozens of different ways,
but we couldn't' get it right.

311
00:11:57,916 --> 00:11:59,583
[SAIKI]
Was that his accident?

312
00:11:59,666 --> 00:12:01,541
[CHOUNO] Fortunately, he only
needed a couple stitches.

313
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:03,750
No, the real problem
came two days after that,

314
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:06,041
when a motorcycle hit him,
throwing him 30 meters.

315
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,458
[SAIKI]
Holy crap.

316
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:09,250
I still don't know
how to do this trick.

317
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:10,916
Now that the world's
abandoned me,

318
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,666
I have to figure out
some way to use it--

319
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,791
[SAIKI] There's actually nothing
to figure out here.

320
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:17,208
There are no moving pieces
or hidden compartments,

321
00:12:17,291 --> 00:12:18,875
just partitions.
It's a box.

322
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:20,541
[chainsaw turns over]

323
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:22,541
[CHOUNO] I'm thinking of using
this in tonight's show

324
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:25,166
then picking a random assistant
from the audience!

325
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:26,666
[SAIKI]
No! No! No!

326
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:29,541
That's how I became
a magician's assistant.

327
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:31,916
[CHOUNO] Midori,
where are you?

328
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,958
No.

329
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:34,166
That's not her.

330
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:36,916
No. Ahh...!
Definitely not.

331
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,166
[SAIKI]
What does his ex even look like?

332
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:41,583
[CHOUNO] No, I have to focus
on my performance.

333
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:44,750
My master is helping,
and I have to impress him, too.

334
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:46,750
Now, for my next
illusion.

335
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,500
I'll move Saichael
from here--

336
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:50,041
[SAIKI]
"Saichael?"

337
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:51,541
[CHOUNO] --over to this box
on the other side

338
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:53,208
--of the stage!
--[audience gasps]

339
00:12:53,291 --> 00:12:55,541
I'll lock both boxes
to keep "Saichael" in

340
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:57,291
and keep everyone else out.

341
00:12:57,375 --> 00:12:59,000
All right, crawl inside.

342
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:01,500
[SAIKI] Okay, but I still
don't know how this works.

343
00:13:01,583 --> 00:13:03,666
When I say so,
pop out of the other box.

344
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,416
Got it? Good!
[SAIKI] No. I do not.

345
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,458
[CHOUNO]
Ladies and gents, I'm closing

346
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:09,333
and locking the box.
Music, please!

347
00:13:09,416 --> 00:13:11,208
[SAIKI]
Seriously? He didn't even

348
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:13,791
bother to explain it.
How am I supposed to--

349
00:13:13,875 --> 00:13:16,208
Well that answers that.
Secret tunnel.

350
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:19,375
I gotta hand it to him,
this is a pretty involved trick.

351
00:13:19,458 --> 00:13:21,916
This must be where I crawl
into the other box.

352
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,250
[creaks]

353
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:26,291
And it won't open.
I'm not surprised.

354
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:28,833
Let's open the box.
And it's tres bien time!

355
00:13:28,916 --> 00:13:30,958
[SAIKI] Fine.
[audience cheers]

356
00:13:31,041 --> 00:13:33,000
[MAN 1]
He just appeared out of nowhere!

357
00:13:33,083 --> 00:13:34,958
[MAN 2] Yeah.
[GIRL] How'd he do that?

358
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:37,333
[CHOUNO] Master came through
for me, but how?

359
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:39,791
So far, tonight's gone
perfect!

360
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:41,000
Did she come?

361
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:45,666
Is that her?
Ahh!

362
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:47,625
Huh...?

363
00:13:47,708 --> 00:13:49,583
[SAIKI] Nendou?
What are you doing here?

364
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:51,833
She's here.
You came back.

365
00:13:51,916 --> 00:13:53,458
You came back for me!

366
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,791
Midori!

367
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,958
[SAIKI]
Huh...?

368
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,916
♪

369
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:03,708
[CHOUNO]
My named used to be

370
00:14:03,791 --> 00:14:05,208
Kouta Nakanishi.

371
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:07,125
I was an office drone
for a book publisher.

372
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:09,416
About a year into the job,
I met Midori.

373
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,458
She worked at the café
one block over.

374
00:14:11,541 --> 00:14:13,541
I still wasn't
very confident at work,

375
00:14:13,625 --> 00:14:15,416
so she was the highlight
of my day.

376
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,583
[sighs]

377
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:17,833
Kouta, welcome!

378
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:19,583
[CHOUNO]
I went as often as I could,

379
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:21,375
until we grew close.

380
00:14:21,458 --> 00:14:24,041
She would smile and listen
as I complained about my job.

381
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,583
Then, one day,
I realized I was in love

382
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,250
and wanted
to take care of her.

383
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,916
Her first husband had died
and she had a son at home.

384
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,500
Anyway, I proposed!

385
00:14:32,583 --> 00:14:33,916
But then--

386
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,625
One month later,
they fired me!

387
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:38,791
I started drinking
and she took her son and left.

388
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:40,333
It's important
she see everything

389
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:42,666
I've accomplished
in the last two years!

390
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:45,375
That's why today's performance
means so much to me!

391
00:14:45,458 --> 00:14:47,458
[SAIKI] Yeah, I get all that,
but in the end,

392
00:14:47,541 --> 00:14:49,541
this Midori person,
never show up.

393
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:51,000
[NENDOU]
Cool, magic knife!

394
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:52,416
I have a magic pencil.

395
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,333
[SAIKI] Instead,
we got this idiot.

396
00:14:54,416 --> 00:14:55,750
Riki, that's not a toy.

397
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,916
--[CHOUNO] Midori!
--[SAIKI] This can't be real.

398
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,208
It's been a while, Kou.

399
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:01,166
[SAIKI]
She's nothing like his memory!

400
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:02,750
Meet my wife.

401
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,500
[SAIKI] These plot twists
are giving me whiplash!

402
00:15:04,583 --> 00:15:07,375
I wish the writer would stop
making stuff up on the fly.

403
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:08,958
--You look familiar.
--[SAIKI] Shoot!

404
00:15:09,041 --> 00:15:11,000
The glasses are all wrong.
For a second

405
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:13,166
I thought you were Saiki,
my best buddy.

406
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:14,541
[SAIKI]
He's so reliably stupid.

407
00:15:14,625 --> 00:15:16,125
Well, that's my cue
to leave.

408
00:15:16,208 --> 00:15:18,250
Whoa, don't go
anywhere yet, Saichael.

409
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,916
We've still got
half of the show!

410
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,250
--[SAIKI] Just my luck.
--[CHOUNO] My sweet,

411
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:23,208
watch the rest
of my performance...

412
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:24,875
then give me
a second chance?

413
00:15:24,958 --> 00:15:26,458
[SAIKI]
This is unfathomably weird.

414
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:28,125
Yes. It's a drive for me
and Riki,

415
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,083
so at the very least
we'll watch you.

416
00:15:30,166 --> 00:15:32,458
But don't expect any more
from me than that.

417
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:35,833
It feels like our relationship
ran its course a long time ago.

418
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:38,250
[SAIKI] Why do you and Nendou
have the same face?

419
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:40,875
Master,
let's get the box ready

420
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:43,375
Presenting, my all-new
body-cutting trick!

421
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:45,583
My lovely assistant
will get inside the box,

422
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:48,000
then separate the box
into parts with a chainsaw!

423
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:49,916
Then I'll move the parts
around stage--

424
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,375
[SAIKI] If you explain
the whole trick

425
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:53,291
before you do it,
where's the surprise?

426
00:15:53,375 --> 00:15:55,125
[MAN 1]
You think this'll really work?

427
00:15:55,208 --> 00:15:56,750
[MAN 2]
It's gotta be a trick box.

428
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,166
[SAIKI]
It's actually not.

429
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,833
This box is literally
just a box.

430
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:01,750
No gimmicks.
Which, would suck for me

431
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:04,166
if I wasn't a psychic.
I've come up with 13 ways

432
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,125
to avoid getting chainsawed
to death.

433
00:16:06,208 --> 00:16:08,708
First, I'll bend the blade
when it cuts into the box.

434
00:16:08,791 --> 00:16:10,416
Then, right before
he pulls it out,

435
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:13,041
I'll turn back time on the blade
to put it back to normal.

436
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:15,958
When he moves the parts around
I'll use my super flexibility.

437
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:17,958
Are you ready, Saichael!
Let's go!

438
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:19,416
[NENDOU]
Hold on!

439
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,166
I wanna be your helper
and get in the box!

440
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:24,708
Try to cut me up
with whatever, I'll be fine!

441
00:16:24,791 --> 00:16:26,208
Riki.
You idiot.

442
00:16:26,291 --> 00:16:27,541
--Wait. No.
--[SAIKI] Sit down!

443
00:16:27,625 --> 00:16:29,625
That's enough, Riki.
Let's go!

444
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:31,750
No! Midori, don't go!

445
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:33,250
[SAIKI]
And just like that,

446
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:34,708
the wheels came off.

447
00:16:34,791 --> 00:16:37,083
Now what's he gonna do?
With Nendou in there,

448
00:16:37,166 --> 00:16:39,583
he's likely to send
the audience home screaming.

449
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,458
[CHOUNO]
The blade won't touch him.

450
00:16:41,541 --> 00:16:42,958
The gimmick will trigger.

451
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:45,208
My love is watching!
Don't kill her son!

452
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:47,333
[NENDOU] Hit me with
that chainsaw, bro!

453
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,708
Riki's my name.
Riki Nendou.

454
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:51,500
I know I look cool.
You just don't get it

455
00:16:51,583 --> 00:16:53,458
'cause you're nothing
but an old grandpa.

456
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:55,333
I'm dropping out of
high school.

457
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:57,958
I gotta earn some cash
to support my mom.

458
00:16:58,041 --> 00:17:01,666
I'm sorry! I can't go through
with this trick!

459
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:04,000
I violated the Code
of Stage Magic.

460
00:17:04,083 --> 00:17:06,208
I wanted this trick
to be a hit so badly,

461
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:08,458
that I brought it out here
even though

462
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,583
I hadn't figured out yet
how to do it, safely. Sorry.

463
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,708
I knew they'd be mad,
but not that mad.

464
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:17,166
[SAIKI]
They full-on rioted.

465
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:19,375
But, I think you made
the right decision.

466
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:21,833
Usually, I can find
a ton of different ways out,

467
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,416
but this time, I only saw
four ways to save Nendou.

468
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,500
--What do I do now?
--[thud]

469
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:28,625
Hey, my old bank account.

470
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:30,958
[MIDORI]
It had gotten lost in my stuff.

471
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:32,708
I never spent one cent from it.

472
00:17:32,791 --> 00:17:34,625
[CHOUNO] Midori!
I thought you left!

473
00:17:34,708 --> 00:17:36,458
Well, that was
a really bad show.

474
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:38,208
You got the crowd
so excited

475
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:40,083
then you didn't
deliver the goods.

476
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:41,750
Is it any wonder
they rioted?

477
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:43,208
But don't worry.

478
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:45,416
When you've got
that trick down cold,

479
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,125
I'll come see it
again.

480
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:48,708
[CHOUNO]
Thanks for my bank account!

481
00:17:48,791 --> 00:17:51,041
I promise I'll do it right
next time!

482
00:17:51,125 --> 00:17:52,791
With this,
I now have the money

483
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:55,125
to buy a brand new,
1.2 million yen box!

484
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:57,416
[MIDORI]
One-point-two million?

485
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,041
[thud]
Ugh!

486
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:02,541
[MIDORI] On second thought,
give that back, loser!

487
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:05,041
[man singing in Japanese]

488
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:09,583
♪

489
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:15,458
Hey, we're all going to karaoke
after class, you wanna come?

490
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:16,958
--[BOY 1] Heck yeah!
--[GIRL] I want in!

491
00:18:17,041 --> 00:18:18,375
[BOY 2]
Let's make it a party!

492
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:20,083
[BOY 3] Hairo! You down
for some karaoke?

493
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:21,916
Now that exams are done,
sure, bro!

494
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,166
--[GIRL] Yumehara, coming?
--[YUMEHARA] Sounds fun!

495
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:26,250
--[BOY 3] Uh, hey.
--[NENDOU] What?

496
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,500
[BOY 3]
Yoshida, are you in?

497
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:29,125
What are they
talking about?

498
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,791
[SAIKI]
It's better that you don't.

499
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,458
[GIRL]
What about you, Mera?

500
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:34,375
Yeah, I have plans later,
sorry.

501
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:36,500
[GIRL]
Interesting. Is it a date?

502
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:38,833
[MERA]
Maybe. Something like that.

503
00:18:38,916 --> 00:18:40,208
[BOYS]
Oh, wow! Teruhashi!

504
00:18:40,291 --> 00:18:41,375
What's up, guys.

505
00:18:41,458 --> 00:18:42,625
[BOY 3]
Wanna come to karaoke?

506
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:43,916
[BOY 1]
Most of the class is going.

507
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,541
Us and the other guys
over there.

508
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,666
[TERUHASHI] Doesn't look like
Saiki's coming, so, no.

509
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:50,625
I'm sorry, I can't. I have
a koto lesson after school.

510
00:18:50,708 --> 00:18:53,083
--[BOY 3] Okay.
--[BOY 1] Let's call it off.

511
00:18:53,166 --> 00:18:55,041
[SAIKI]
Wow, that sure killed the mood.

512
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:56,708
This is Café Mami.

513
00:18:56,791 --> 00:18:58,291
It's quiet,
out of the way,

514
00:18:58,375 --> 00:19:00,625
and very relaxing,
which makes me a regular.

515
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:03,291
Most importantly,
they serve great coffee jelly.

516
00:19:03,375 --> 00:19:04,875
Since this is a coffee shop,

517
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:06,916
it puts the store bought
ones to shame.

518
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,791
It is one of life's
great pleasures.

519
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:11,208
Unfortunately,
I may have to stop coming here.

520
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:12,750
[MERA]
Sorry, to keep you waiting.

521
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,000
Ahh! Saiki?

522
00:19:14,083 --> 00:19:15,666
[clatter]

523
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,708
[SAIKI] What a waste.
And it was such good coffee.

524
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,833
At least I was able
to catch my coffee jelly.

525
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:22,083
Why not, she'd just
have to throw it away.

526
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:25,833
Sorry! I'll clean up
and get you another one,

527
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:28,333
just hold on--
Hey, where's the jelly?

528
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:30,208
[SAIKI]
No idea.

529
00:19:30,291 --> 00:19:32,208
I'm sorry.
I can be a bit of a klutz.

530
00:19:32,291 --> 00:19:33,666
[SAIKI]
No complaints here.

531
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,291
[MERA]
Here's an extra, free of charge.

532
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,541
[SAIKI]
Are you a god?

533
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:38,583
Um, by the way,
Saiki?

534
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:41,916
[SAIKI] Mera Chisato, I know why
you panicked when you saw me.

535
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,625
I'm begging!
Please don't tell anyone

536
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:45,541
that I've got a part-time job
as a waitress!

537
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:47,416
If the school finds out,
they'll make me quit.

538
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,958
[SAIKI]
Student jobs are forbidden.

539
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:50,666
[MERA] Not just this job,
but my morning paper

540
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:51,916
milk-delivery routes,

541
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,166
my night job
at the gas station,

542
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:54,541
and the restaurant.

543
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:55,958
Not to mention my gigs

544
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:57,875
as a baby-sitter, tutor,
and flower arranger!

545
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,166
[SAIKI]
Making her quit seems humane.

546
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,666
To be honest,
my family's poor.

547
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,458
[SAIKI] I think everyone
all ready knew that.

548
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:05,416
Her lunch is always just rice
with a pickled plum.

549
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,750
Her gym clothes have
someone else's name on them.

550
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:10,291
And, if you look closely,
her glasses are missing a lens!

551
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:12,291
And right now,
she's literally drooling

552
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:14,083
over my coffee jelly.

553
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:16,375
Oh, it's fine.
You can go ahead and eat.

554
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:20,958
[SAIKI] You're hard to ignore.
Besides, your drool ruined it.

555
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,750
Mm!

556
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:25,375
Saiki, it's so good!
I feel like I owe you my life.

557
00:20:25,458 --> 00:20:27,958
All I've had to eat since
yesterday morning is ice!

558
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,708
[SAIKI] If coffee jelly's the
price of survival, so be it.

559
00:20:30,791 --> 00:20:33,500
I'm supporting everyone!
So that's why you can't blab

560
00:20:33,583 --> 00:20:35,208
about me working.
Is that okay?

561
00:20:35,291 --> 00:20:37,250
Ugh! Three-second-rule!

562
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,625
[SAIKI] Okay. I promise
not to tell anyone.

563
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,208
[MERA]
Thank you, Saiki!

564
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:43,750
[SAIKI] Keeping her secret
benefits me, too.

565
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:46,083
It means I get
to keep coming here.

566
00:20:46,166 --> 00:20:47,250
[door opens]

567
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:48,875
--[MERA] Welcome!
--[SAIKI] Huh?

568
00:20:48,958 --> 00:20:50,041
Wait.

569
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:51,875
[Mera groaning]

570
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:54,416
[MERA]
Mister Matsuzaki?

571
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,458
Young lady,
are you working here?

572
00:20:56,541 --> 00:20:58,250
[SAIKI] It is him.
Sorry, I don't think

573
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:00,416
there's anything
I can do to help you.

574
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:02,041
Don't take it personally.

575
00:21:02,125 --> 00:21:03,958
Are you working here,
yes or no?

576
00:21:04,041 --> 00:21:04,958
[MERA] N-no.

577
00:21:05,041 --> 00:21:05,958
[MATSUZAKI]
You know the rules.

578
00:21:06,041 --> 00:21:07,458
No matter how good
your reason--

579
00:21:07,541 --> 00:21:09,291
[MERA] If they won't let
me help my family,

580
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:10,666
I'll have to quit
school!

581
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:12,208
Nothing to worry
about, Mera.

582
00:21:12,291 --> 00:21:13,583
You're working hard,
huh?

583
00:21:13,666 --> 00:21:15,041
Thank you so much,
sir!

584
00:21:15,125 --> 00:21:16,791
[MATSUZAKI] Well, I'd
like to order a parfait.

585
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,666
[MERA]
Coming right up!

586
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:21,333
[SAIKI] Well, I said I'd keep
my mind control powers sealed,

587
00:21:21,416 --> 00:21:23,833
but I guess I made
another change in the world.

588
00:21:23,916 --> 00:21:25,166
Not a big one, though.

589
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:27,125
Hopefully it won't affect
too much.

590
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:28,791
[PEOPLE]
PK Academy students

591
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:31,083
are now allowed
to have after-school jobs.

592
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:33,083
[SAIKI] Consider this thanks
for the coffee jelly.

593
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:36,708
Hey, we're all going to karaoke
after class, you wanna come?

594
00:21:36,791 --> 00:21:38,333
Now that exams are done,
sure, bro!

595
00:21:38,416 --> 00:21:39,500
Sounds like fun!

596
00:21:39,583 --> 00:21:40,666
What.

597
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,041
[BOY]
Hey Mera, are you in?

598
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:44,291
Thanks, but I have work
after school.

599
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:45,541
Instead of karaoke,

600
00:21:45,625 --> 00:21:46,916
how 'bout we all go
to your work

601
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:47,958
to keep you company?

602
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:50,208
[MERA]
That'd be great!

603
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:52,041
[BOY 1] We're going
to Mera's work.

604
00:21:52,125 --> 00:21:53,625
Do you wanna come?

605
00:21:53,708 --> 00:21:55,416
Well. Today, I might be.

606
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:56,958
Saiki's not going, is he?

607
00:21:57,041 --> 00:21:58,625
[BOY 2] Saiki says
he wants to come!

608
00:21:58,708 --> 00:22:00,125
Aah! Saiki? Yeah, sure!

609
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:01,583
I'm in, let's go!

610
00:22:01,666 --> 00:22:03,000
--[BOY 1] Really?
--[BOY 2] Suh-weet!

611
00:22:03,083 --> 00:22:04,666
Oh, hey, what's going on?

612
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:07,208
We finally gonna get together
after school and hang?

613
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:08,458
[BOY]
Nendou wants to come?

614
00:22:08,541 --> 00:22:09,708
[GIRL]
Let's just cancel.

615
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:11,791
[SAIKI]
Wow, that sure killed the mood.

616
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:15,333
♪

617
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,666
[woman singing in Japanese]

618
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,666
[SAIKI]
We introduced so many

619
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:45,208
new characters this episode.

620
00:23:45,291 --> 00:23:47,583
I'm exhausted.
I think I'll unwind with--

621
00:23:47,666 --> 00:23:49,500
Surprise!
--a coffee jelly!

622
00:23:49,583 --> 00:23:52,583
Next time, on
<i>The Disastrous Life of Saiki K:</i>

623
00:23:52,666 --> 00:23:54,833
Hoo, boy. I just foresaw
what'll happen.

624
00:23:54,916 --> 00:23:56,208
What a pain.

